Gideon Argov: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 8:39 PM ET
Electrical Equipment

Company Overview of Poco Graphite, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Gideon   Argov  Chief Executive Officer of Entegris Inc, President of Entegris Inc and Director of Entegris Inc, Poco Graphite, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 15 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Gideon Argov has been an Advisory Director at Berkshire Partners LLC since May 6, 2013. Mr. Argov served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Entegris Inc. from August 2005 to November 2012. Mr. Argov served as a Director of Entegris Inc. from 2004 to November 2012. He was an Advisory Partner at Castle Island Partners LLC. Mr. Argov served as Chief Executive Officer at Mykrolis Corp. since November 22, 2004. Prior to joining Mykrolis, he served as a Special ... Limited Partner at Parthenon Capital, LLC since 2001 and served as its Managing Director. He was a Special Limited Partner at Parthenon Capital Partners. Previously, Mr. Argov served as Managing Director of Operations at Parthenon Capital from 2001 to November 2004. Prior to joining Parthenon Capital in 2001, Mr. Argov served as President and Chief Executive Officer at Kollmorgen Corporation from November 1991 to 2000. He served as the Chairman of Kollmorgen Corporation from March 26, 1996 to 2000 and Vice Chairman from May 23, 1991 to November 1991. He served as a Director of Kollmorgen Corporation since May 23, 1991. Prior to joining Kollmorgen, Mr. Argov served as the President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman at High Voltage Engineering Corporation from 1988 to May 1991. From 1983 to 1988, he led engagement teams in consulting at Bain and Company. Mr. Argov was a Partner and Managing Director of Transtechnology Corporation USA. Mr. Argov also served as a combat officer and Company Commander in the armored corps of the Israel Defense Forces. He served as the Chairman of Zik Energy Points, Inc. since January 3, 2013 and also served as its Member of Advisory Board. Mr. Argov has been a Director of X-Rite, Incorporated since July 2006. He serves as Director of Kollmorgen Servotronix Ltd., Tech/Ops Sevcon Inc., and Servotronix,and. He serves as a Director of RWL Water LLC. He is a member of the Council on Foreign Relations and the International Council of the Belfer Center at the John F. Kennedy School of Government, Harvard University. He served as a Director of J.M. Huber Corporation (also known as Huber (J.M.) Corp.) until July 2015. He served as a Director of SunEdison Semiconductor Limited from May 2014 to December 2, 2016. He was a Director of Beechcraft Corporation since February 15, 2013. He served as Member of Advisory Board of Zik Energy Points, Inc. Mr. Argov served as a Director of Interline Brands Inc. and Interline Brands, Inc., a New Jersey Corporation from June 2004 to September 7, 2012 and for its subsidiary, Interline Opco since August 2001 until September 7, 2012. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Fundtech Ltd. from July 22, 2003 to February 18, 2009 and served as its Vice Chairman since February 17, 2009. He served as a Non-Executive Director of Amazys Holding GmbH since 1997. Mr. Argov served as a Director of Fundtech Ltd since July 22, 2003. He served as a Director of Helix Technology Corporation since 2002. Mr. Argov served as a Director of Mykrolis Corporation since November 22, 2004. He served as a Director of Breeze-Eastern Corporation from 1995 to February 11, 2005 and WorldCorp, Inc. since August 23, 1995. He was a Director at L-3 Communications SSG-Tinsley Inc., Beechcraft LLC and XRITE. Mr. Argov was awarded his M.B.A. from Stanford University in 1983 and received A.B. magnum cum laude in Economics from Harvard University.Read Full Background




